39:46.135 --> 39:48.345
To analyze the atmosphere and find planets

39:48.429 --> 39:50.014
that match the different requirements.

39:50.097 --> 39:53.100
1,300 planets were identified,
but only two confirmed.

39:53.184 --> 39:54.894
And of those two,

39:54.977 --> 39:57.438
one turned out to be something.

39:57.605 --> 39:59.023
- Radioactive.
- Yeah.

39:59.106 --> 40:01.609
So right now that leaves one planet

40:01.692 --> 40:04.028
in all of space that's perfect.

40:05.404 --> 40:07.364
You're talking about
what I think you're talking about, right?

40:07.448 --> 40:08.949
- I probably am.
- All right.

40:09.033 --> 40:10.117
Okay.

40:10.201 --> 40:11.994
How'd the date with the Giant go last night?

40:12.078 --> 40:14.246
Not that good.
