41:36.745 --> 41:37.788
Mmm.

41:37.872 --> 41:40.040
You can sit right there, sir.

41:42.001 --> 41:44.712
You understand we're going
to ask about Operation Genoa

41:44.795 --> 41:46.839
- and that it was a classified mission?
- Yes.

41:46.922 --> 41:50.092
Okay, you're all set.

41:50.176 --> 41:52.094
I'm stepping out.

41:52.928 --> 41:54.638
JERRY: And you're going to
confirm it happened.

41:54.722 --> 41:56.140
STOMTONOVICH: It happened.

42:01.103 --> 42:03.314
JERRY: What was Operation Genoa?

42:03.397 --> 42:04.732
An extraction.

42:04.815 --> 42:08.527
Two Marines were taken by the enemy
and I won't say more than that.

42:08.611 --> 42:10.404
Who carried out the extraction?

42:10.487 --> 42:13.032
MARSOC, Marines Special
Operations Command.

42:13.115 --> 42:15.659
Were any exceptional measures
used in the operation?

42:15.743 --> 42:17.745
Exceptional measures were called for.

42:17.828 --> 42:19.330
Were they used?

42:25.544 --> 42:26.712
General?

42:27.630 --> 42:28.881
(SIGHS)

42:30.883 --> 42:33.761
- Was sarin gas used during Genoa?
- It is right.

42:33.844 --> 42:37.056
It is moral and necessary to
use any means in that situation,

42:37.139 --> 42:39.516
in the situation they were in, to use the means

42:39.600 --> 42:41.727
at your disposal to rescue captured prisoners.

42:41.810 --> 42:44.730
- Did we use sarin gas?
- If we used sarin, let me put it this way.

42:44.813 --> 42:46.857
- Sir.
- Here's how we would have used sarin.

42:46.941 --> 42:48.359
I'd like to get to the logistics in a moment,

42:48.442 --> 42:51.570
but right now I'm asking you
if we used sarin gas.

42:51.654 --> 42:54.073
If we used sarin...

42:54.156 --> 42:55.741
- General...
- Listen to me.

42:55.824 --> 43:00.246
If we used sarin, here's how we used sarin.

43:01.997 --> 43:04.583
It would have been stockpiled
in a depot in Okinawa.

43:04.667 --> 43:06.460
That's first. It was guarded...

43:12.174 --> 43:14.677
<i>- Two Marines...</i>
- (FAST-FORWARDING)

43:15.052 --> 43:18.138
JERRY ON TAPE:...<i>we used sarin gas?</i>
STOMTONOVICH: <i>If we used sarin...</i>

43:18.222 --> 43:19.723
JERRY: <i>General...</i>
STOMTONOVICH: <i>Listen to me.</i>

43:19.807 --> 43:24.395
<i>If we used sarin, here's how we used sarin.</i>

43:24.478 --> 43:25.771
(REWINDING)

43:26.188 --> 43:30.818
<i>If we used sarin, here's how we used sarin.</i>

43:31.819 --> 43:33.404
<i>...how we used sarin.</i>

43:33.487 --> 43:35.656
<i>...how we used sarin.</i>

43:37.283 --> 43:39.118
<i>...we used sarin.</i>

43:43.247 --> 43:45.499
<i>It is right. It is moral and...</i>

43:45.582 --> 43:46.709
(REWINDING)

43:46.792 --> 43:48.544
<i>It is moral and...</i>

43:49.962 --> 43:51.297
JERRY ON TAPE:
<i>Who carried out the extraction?</i>

43:51.380 --> 43:54.550
STOMTONOVICH: <i>MARSOC, Marines Special</i>
<i>Operations Command.</i>

43:54.633 --> 43:56.468
JERRY: <i>Did we use sarin gas?</i>

43:56.552 --> 43:58.304
STOMTONOVICH: <i>We used sarin.</i>

43:58.387 --> 43:59.805
JERRY: <i>And how is that used?</i>

43:59.888 --> 44:02.558
STOMTONOVICH: <i>Here's how we used sarin.</i>

44:04.101 --> 44:05.644
<i>It would have been stockpiled...</i>

44:05.728 --> 44:08.188
- I want to see the raw footage.
- CHARLIE: Yeah.

44:08.897 --> 44:10.232
(TYPING)

44:16.405 --> 44:17.740
Here we go.

44:18.866 --> 44:21.952
JERRY ON TAPE: <i>Were any exceptional</i>
<i>measures used in the operation?</i>

44:22.036 --> 44:23.912
STOMTONOVICH: <i>Exceptional measures</i>
<i>were called for.</i>

44:24.038 --> 44:25.247
JERRY: <i>Like what?</i>

44:28.250 --> 44:29.752
<i>We used sarin.</i>

44:29.835 --> 44:32.254
<i>It is right. It is moral and...</i>

44:36.342 --> 44:37.676
We're not there yet.

44:39.803 --> 44:42.056
- You're joking, right?
- CHARLIE: It's compelling film.

44:42.139 --> 44:43.223
Compelling?

44:43.307 --> 44:44.808
When Mac and I showed up
at his house yesterday,

44:44.892 --> 44:46.852
he'd forgotten he'd talked to us on the phone.

44:46.935 --> 44:49.355
He thought we were selling
magazine subscriptions.

44:49.438 --> 44:51.523
(STAMMERING)
He wasn't being asked about...

44:51.607 --> 44:53.609
Did it seem to you like he was shaky during...

44:53.692 --> 44:55.194
I want another witness.

44:55.277 --> 44:57.196
- We have our key witness.
- He wasn't there.

44:57.279 --> 44:58.781
- JERRY: He knew about it.
- Didn't remember we'd called.

44:58.864 --> 45:00.616
- He didn't remember at first, right?
- MACKENZIE: Jerry...

45:00.699 --> 45:03.869
JERRY: We've got evidence of a war crime.
Just sit with that for a second.

45:04.370 --> 45:07.498
We dropped sarin gas on a village.

45:10.084 --> 45:12.044
We have a moral imperative to question

45:12.127 --> 45:14.463
the flagrant disregard
with which the president

45:14.546 --> 45:16.131
and the national security establishment

45:16.215 --> 45:18.717
treat the Constitution and international laws.

45:18.801 --> 45:20.260
What does this have to do
with the Constitution?

45:20.344 --> 45:22.721
We've killed four American citizens
without due process.

45:22.805 --> 45:24.223
And those are the ones we know about.

45:24.306 --> 45:28.143
Five times as many drone strikes
as the entire Bush presidency.

45:28.227 --> 45:32.398
Dramatically increased wiretapping,
detentions, prosecuting whistle blowers,

45:32.481 --> 45:34.900
several of whom
are willing to go on camera for us.

45:34.983 --> 45:36.944
- What your problem is...
- Careful, Jerry.

45:37.027 --> 45:39.405
...is that you like him. You like this president.

45:39.488 --> 45:41.949
You trust him. Go ahead, we trust you.

45:42.032 --> 45:45.202
Chase Nielsen flew
the Doolittle Raid after Pearl Harbor

45:45.285 --> 45:47.162
and got water boarded by the Japanese,

45:47.246 --> 45:49.581
and we executed
the Japanese soldiers who did it!

45:49.665 --> 45:51.375
What the fuck is going on?

45:51.708 --> 45:52.751
We have it.

45:55.754 --> 45:57.423
How long before you're comfortable?

45:59.174 --> 46:02.845
Former Pennsylvania Senator Rick Santorum
suspended his campaign for the presidency...

46:02.928 --> 46:05.305
President Obama told ABC News'
Robin Roberts

46:05.389 --> 46:07.808
that same-sex couples
should be able to get married.

46:07.891 --> 46:09.935
Texas Representative Ron Paul said today

46:10.018 --> 46:12.896
that he will stop actively campaigning
in the Republican primaries.

46:12.980 --> 46:14.773
And now, thanks to the Lone Star State,

46:14.857 --> 46:17.109
Governor Romney
can officially drop the word "presumptive."

46:17.192 --> 46:19.445
Wisconsin Governor Scott Walker
is still the governor...

46:19.528 --> 46:21.155
Chick-Fil-A's president, Dan Cathy said,

46:21.238 --> 46:23.657
"I think we are inviting
God's judgment on our nation."

46:23.740 --> 46:25.784
The White House is exercising
executive privilege

46:25.868 --> 46:28.454
over documents requested by
the House Oversight Committee

46:28.537 --> 46:30.330
in its investigation of "Fast and Furious."

46:30.414 --> 46:32.583
Chief Justice John Roberts...
...wrote the majority opinion

46:32.666 --> 46:34.376
in the historic 5-4 decision.

46:34.501 --> 46:37.212
The constitutionality of the Affordable Care
Act has been challenged...

46:37.296 --> 46:39.798
With eight weeks left until the Republican
National Convention in Tampa,

46:39.882 --> 46:42.468
speculation has turned to Governor Romney's
choice of running mate.

46:42.551 --> 46:44.553
<i>...introduced Representative Paul Ryan,</i>

46:44.636 --> 46:47.514
<i>one of the Republican party's young</i>
<i>conservative leaders as his running mate.</i>

46:47.598 --> 46:50.392
Representative Todd Akin,
who won Missouri's GOP Senate primary

46:50.476 --> 46:53.812
earlier this month, and who will face
Democratic incumbent Claire McCaskill,

46:53.896 --> 46:56.356
said Sunday that he misspoke
when he claimed "legitimate rape"...

46:56.440 --> 46:59.526
With three days to go before delegates
converge on Tampa Bay, Florida,

46:59.610 --> 47:01.904
GOP officials are moving
forward with their plans

47:01.987 --> 47:04.740
to kick off the Republican
National Convention on Monday,

47:04.823 --> 47:07.493
despite the looming threat
of Tropical Storm Isaac.

47:07.868 --> 47:10.287
<i>The storm is currently headed for Haiti.</i>

47:10.370 --> 47:13.832
I'm gonna ask you to hold on
just a second, please.

47:15.876 --> 47:17.669
(WHISPERING)

47:39.525 --> 47:40.817
(KNOCKING ON GLASS)

