Lance Corporal Herman Valenzuela
is on the phone.

47:52.788 --> 47:54.414
Valenzuela is dead.

47:55.040 --> 47:57.251
No, he's not. He's on the phone.

47:57.918 --> 47:59.711
How'd you get that wrong?

47:59.795 --> 48:03.799
There were two Herman Valenzuelas.
Both lance corporals.

48:03.882 --> 48:05.425
One was killed in action.

48:05.509 --> 48:07.553
Why were you calling him
if you thought he was dead?

48:07.636 --> 48:10.264
The messages were left
for him before we got the service records.

48:10.347 --> 48:12.766
We stopped calling, but he'd been deployed.

48:12.849 --> 48:15.394
And when he got home,
he got our messages and returned our call.

48:15.477 --> 48:17.145
And that's when you gave the green light?

48:17.229 --> 48:19.022
We had Sweeney, we had Hamni8...

48:19.147 --> 48:20.899
- Charlie.
- ...we had the report from the NGO,

48:20.983 --> 48:22.693
- we had my source...
- Who you won't reveal.

48:22.776 --> 48:24.027
...we had the helo manifest,

48:24.111 --> 48:26.363
we had Valenzuela who was the crew chief.

48:26.446 --> 48:31.577
We had a story that the US used sarin gas
on a village in Pakistan and we went.

48:31.660 --> 48:32.703
Anybody would have.

48:32.786 --> 48:35.122
Most people would have gone months earlier.

48:35.205 --> 48:40.002
To not go would have been to participate
in the biggest cover-up since...

48:42.546 --> 48:44.590
These were war crimes.

48:48.010 --> 48:50.887
It was a Sunday special report.
9:00 p.m. Eastern.

48:50.971 --> 48:53.724
Nielsen tracking showed
it was gonna be a monster audience,

48:53.807 --> 48:55.559
three and a half, four million.

48:55.642 --> 48:57.853
It ended up closer to six.

48:59.813 --> 49:02.316
By 10:05, I knew we had a problem.

49:04.526 --> 49:06.445
None of it was true.
